      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="238">Metallic beryllium is produced by the electrolysis of a molten mixture of beryllium chloride - </text>
      <subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="238">BeCl</text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="13" fc="0" fa="1" charset="238"></text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="238">2</text>
      </subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0"> and sodium chloride - NaCl - a</text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="238">t a temperature of about </text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0">1350 </text>
      <text fn="Symbol" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="2">°</text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0">C. Sodium chloride is added to improve the electrical conductivity of the mixture. Another method of metallic </text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="238">beryllium preparation involves the reduction of beryllium fluoride - </text>
      <subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="238">BeF</text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="13" fc="0" fa="1" charset="238"></text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="238">2</text>
      </subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0"> - by magnesium.</text>
   </par>
